T|Novi|0|Situation: The an pipeline is effectively offline. socialsnapshots contains 0 rows — no historical snapshots exist to establish baselines or detect anomalies. socialposts holds only 2 records, both from February 2025 (Instagram launch posts, 7–11 likes, <0.17% engagement). No data newer than 16 months. The 10 tracked cr all show zero movement across every metric (follower growth, traffic spikes, viral cn, share of voice, WoW change) — the cr tracker is connected to the db but not producing differentiated signals.
T|Novi|1|
T|Novi|2|Diagnosis: This is not a lo-engagement problem; it's a data ingestion fl. We cannot assess whether nz is gaining or losing ground bc the measurement instruments are dark. The base rate for a functioning sl an stack is that fresh snapshots arrive at least weekly — we're at zero. Confidence in any tn statement is therefore negligible. The two existing posts serve only as a proof that sb connectivity worked at some point in May 2026 (both have created_at of 2026-05-28), suggesting a manual backfill or tst insert, not an active pipeline.
T|Novi|3|
T|Novi|4|Action: Connect sl data ingestion. The single highest-leverage move is getting social_snapshots populating — whether via Apify actors (Instagram scrapers), the YouTube ap, or manual CSV import. w/o snapshots, every mk decision (ro's ad spend, ln's cn calendar, nt's growth levers) is flying blind. The sb connection works — the problem is upstream.
T|Novi|5|
T|Novi|6|Confidence: hi on the diagnosis (the numbers speak clearly: zero data = broken pipeline); lo on specific remedies (we don't know whether the blockage is ap key expiration, rate limiting, or a script that was never deployed).
