T|Hour|0|Situation: Complete data blackout. Zero sl posts. Zero sl snapshots. Zero cr tracked. Every table that carries competitive or sl intelligence for hb is empty. The vt record exists in the db (created 2026-03-22, status "active", operating in Canada) but has no an instrumentation whatsoever.
T|Hour|1|
T|Hour|2|Diagnosis: hb was created in the sy as a vt entity but never wired into the an layer. This is consistent w/ a B2B SaaS go-to-mk motion — sl media metrics may be less relevant than for a DTC br — but the absence of any cr tracking or mk intelligence means we have no quantitative basis for st decisions. The gap is structural, not temporary.
T|Hour|3|
T|Hour|4|Action: Define hb's minimum an footprint. Before building pipelines, decide what matters: for a fintech SaaS targeting Canada, the signals are likely LinkedIn engagement, GitHub stars/pd metrics, funding rounds in the competitive set, and maybe Twitter/X fintech discourse. Define 3–5 key metrics and the data sources to feed them. Then im the smallest possible pipeline (one cr, one data source) to prove the loop.
T|Hour|5|
T|Hour|6|Confidence: md. The diagnosis is clear from the data vacuum, but the correct instrumentation depends on pd stage and GTM st — variables this brief cannot resolve from db queries alone.
