T|Cros|0|Both vt share the same root problem: the an stack exists structurally (tables defined, sb connected) but is not operational. This is not a vt-specific fl — it's an infrastructure gap. The yv OS has a dashboard layer (app/screens/an/) and db tables but no active data ingestion btw them. For mc: this means all dashboards showing zeros are accurate — the data literally isn't there — not a rendering bug. The fix is pipeline engineering, not dashboard fixes.
T|Cros|1|
T|Cros|2|The most efficient path is to fix both vt w/ a single ingestion architecture: one cron-triggered script that collects sl + cr data per vt, writes to the canonical sb tables, and has the social_snapshots table serve as the historical record for anomaly detection. Get one vt working and the other follows w/ minimal adaptation.
